[5x QUESTION] does 3D give the ~5x needed for room-T?
  2D kagome/Lieb fell x4.7-5.6 SHORT. The 3D lever above is L_3D=1.84x.
  => 3D ALONE provides ~1.8x, NOT the full ~5x. Closes ~21% of the gap.
  Combined with a higher-<g> isolated 3D flat band it could approach it, BUT:
  HONEST WALL (d6): pyrochlore native flat band is GAPLESS (touching, see gap col)
  -> its D_s is contaminated; only the SOC-gapped variant has trustworthy stiffness,
  and gapping costs <g>. No free 5x. Report L_3D as a real but partial lever.
